<%= stylesheet_link_tag "help.css" %>
<body class="default">
 
<br><br><h1>Help</h1>
<hr>
 
<div class="container">
 
    <div class="panel-group" id="accordion">
        <div class="faqHeader">General questions</div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseOne">Is account registration required?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseOne" class="panel-collapse collapse in">
                <div class="panel-body black">
                    Yes! By signing up, you will get access to other user education profiles and find your best tutor/student 
                    according to your needs.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTen">Do I have to update my profile information?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseTen" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body black">
                    You are not required to do so. However, it is highly recommended because  users search for tutors/users
                    based on education profile provided by others. By sharing your education information, you enable others to know
                    which subjects you need tutoring on or are available in tutoring, allowing them to contact you more easily.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseEleven">Is this free?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseEleven" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body black">
					Yes! We are students and we know how hard classes can be. Our purpose is to help UCLA students on their
                	coursework by providing this platform to match students and tutors, therefore we do not charge anything.                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
 
        <div class="faqHeader">Tutors</div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTwo">Who can be a tutor?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body black">
					Anyone! The knowledge you've gained from any class you have taken can greatly
                    help someone else who is currently taking that class.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseThree">How can I be a tutor?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseThree" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body black">
                    Simply sign up, and search for users that need help in a subject that you are available in tutoring. You can
                    search by user, department, and course. When you have found a user that needs tutoring in a subject you can tutor,
                     simply click their profile and request to be a tutor or message them through chat.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
 
        <div class="faqHeader">Students</div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseFour">How do I get a tutor?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseFour" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body black">
                    Here are some things you can do:
                    <ul>
                    	<li>Update your education profile to let other users know what classes you've taken and your background</li>
                    	<li>Use the search bar at the top, search for the class you need tutoring in</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
 
